In [2]:
def DataPreparation(BOW_OBJECT,LABEL_ENCODE_OBJ,DATA):
    data_Desc_CV = BOW_OBJECT.fit_transform(DATA['Item_Description'])
    DATA.fit_transform=LABEL_ENCODE_OBJ.fit_transform(DATA['Product_Category'])
    DATA['Item_Description']=DATA['Item_Description'].apply(lambda x: " ".join(x for x in x.split() if x not in stop))
    DATA['Item_Description'] =DATA['Item_Description'].str.replace('[^\w\s]','')
    Final_Data = pd.concat([DATA[['Inv_Amt',"Product_Category"]],pd.DataFrame(data_Desc_CV.toarray())],axis=1)
    return Final_Data

Five Fold Cross Validation¶

In [47]:
kfold=KFold(n_splits=5)
In [48]:
scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=kfold,scoring="accuracy",n_jobs=-1)
In [49]:
for i,fold_res in enumerate(scores):
    print("**Fold-{}** Accuracy: {}".format(i+1,round(fold_res,3)))

**Fold-1** Accuracy: 0.998
**Fold-2** Accuracy: 0.998
**Fold-3** Accuracy: 1.0
**Fold-4** Accuracy: 0.999
**Fold-5** Accuracy: 0.998

On Each and every Fold we are getting around same accuracy with Minor varience. So our Classifier is doing good job!
